HEADWORD: Pock
<hw>Pock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>pokke</ets>,
AS. <ets>pocc</ets>, <ets>poc</ets>; akin to D. <ets>pok</ets>, G.
<ets>pocke</ets>, and perh. to E. <ets>poke</ets> a pocket. Cf.
<er>Pox</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A pustule raised on the
surface of the body in variolous and vaccine diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of <qex>pokkes</qex> and of scab every sore.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pockarred</ent>⟦br⟧
